article.headline: Denver 75, New Mexico State 73
article.story: DENVER (AP) -- John Nicholson scored a career-high 34 points, three in the last two minute as Denver rallied to beat New Mexico State 75-73 Thursday night. Trailing by a point, Nicholson tied the game with a free throw then gave Denver (12-7, 7-1 Sun Belt Conference) a 74-72 lead with a short jumper with 49 seconds left. New Mexico State (5-16, 1-7) had three chances to tie or take the lead the rest of the way. Josh Jenkins, who had 13 points, made 1-of-2 free throws to make it 74-73. Then, after Rodney Billups missed a layup, Jenkins lost the ball on an unforced turnover with 9 seconds left. New Mexico had one last chance but Byron Davis missed a wide open 3-pointer at the buzzer. Denver, which hadn't beaten New Mexico State in Denver since Jan. 22, 1966, trailed by 12 points at halftime. They trailed 72-63 after Duane John, who had 22 points, hit a jumper with 4:54 left. But New Mexico State went scoreless and Denver went on an 11-0 run to take the lead before Jenkins broke the Aggies' scoring drought in the final minute. John had 16 points by halftime and New Mexico State shot 61 percent in the first half to lead 50-38 at the break. Erik Benzil went 6-for-18 and finished with 17 points for Denver.
